\section{Combining configured and command-line tutorial paths}

Embedded hosts may configure tutorial paths up front, while the standalone
CLI should also accept them on the command line.  The effective path set
is simply the configured tuple followed by any extra command-line paths.

<<functions>>=
def effective_tutorial_paths(
    configured_paths: tuple[str | Path, ...],
    command_paths: tuple[str | Path, ...],
) -> tuple[str | Path, ...]:
    """Return the combined tutorial paths for one command invocation."""

    return tuple(configured_paths) + tuple(command_paths)
@


\section{Selecting built-in tutorial sets}

The standalone command and embedded hosts should not expose the same
default catalog.

The standalone [[tutorial]] command should feel ready to use on first
launch, so it gets the full packaged sequence.  Embedded hosts are
different: the host decides which application-specific tutorials to add,
but the universal usage tutorial should still come first so students see
the common interaction model before the host-specific lessons.

Command-line [[--tutorial-path]] additions remain explicit extras.  They
come after the configured defaults so packaged onboarding still appears
first in the list.

User-installed tutorials belong only to the standalone command.  Embedded
hosts should remain self-contained so they can control exactly which
tutorials they expose.

<<functions>>=
def user_tutorial_dir() -> Path:
    """Return the directory for user-installed tutorials."""

    return (
        platformdirs.user_data_path(
            "tutorial",
            appauthor=False,
            ensure_exists=False,
        )
        / "tutorials"
    )
@

<<functions>>=
def installed_tutorial_paths() -> tuple[Path, ...]:
    """Return the standalone paths for user-installed tutorials."""

    tutorial_dir = user_tutorial_dir()
    if not tutorial_dir.is_dir():
        return ()
    if not any(path.is_file() for path in tutorial_dir.rglob("*.md")):
        return ()
    return (tutorial_dir,)
@

<<functions>>=
def standalone_tutorial_paths() -> tuple[Path, ...]:
    """Return the default tutorial paths for the standalone CLI."""

    return effective_tutorial_paths(
        builtin_tutorial_paths(),
        installed_tutorial_paths(),
    )
@

<<functions>>=
def embedded_tutorial_paths(
    tutorial_paths: tuple[str | Path, ...],
) -> tuple[str | Path, ...]:
    """Return host tutorial paths prefixed by the universal tutorial."""

    return effective_tutorial_paths((universal_tutorial_path(),), tutorial_paths)
@

