\section{Formatting the review output}

Review is small by design, but it still needs enough structure that a
student can distinguish one step's transcript from the next.

Rich helps with the headings and spacing, but the transcript itself is
not authored Markdown.  It may be shell output or saved file contents, so
review must print it literally rather than treating square brackets or
similar text as Rich markup.

<<functions>>=
def render_review_output(
    console: Console,
    tutorial_title: str,
    run_id: str,
    workspace: str,
    transcripts: tuple[StepTranscript, ...],
) -> None:
    """Render formatted review output for saved transcripts."""

    console.print()
    console.print(tutorial_title, style="bold")
    console.print(f"Run: {run_id}", style="dim")
    console.print(f"Workspace: {workspace}", style="dim")
    for transcript in transcripts:
        status = "pass" if transcript.passed else "not yet complete"
        console.print()
        console.print(
            f"Step {transcript.step_index + 1}: {transcript.title}",
            style="bold",
        )
        console.print(f"Status: {status}", style="dim")
        if transcript.edited_file:
            console.print(f"Edited file: {transcript.edited_file}", style="dim")
        console.print(
            transcript.transcript.rstrip("\n"),
            highlight=False,
            markup=False,
        )
    console.print()
@

